    <title>DFDL WG - document #357: Remove bi-directional support from DFDL 1.0</title>
    <link rel="alternate" href="https://redmine.ogf.org/issues/357"/>
    <id>https://redmine.ogf.org/issues/357?journal_id=1305</id>
    <updated>2019-09-27T04:25:25-04:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Steve Hanson</name>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Something to consider when removing bidi support. IBM DFDL recognises dfdl:textBidi and checks that it is 'no' - unsupported error otherwise. Consequently there is an occurrence of dfdl:textBidi='no' in every dfdl:format annotation generated by the New DFDL Schema wizard that comes with IBM DFDL. So implementations will still need to recognise dfdl:textBidi and ignore it.&lt;/p&gt;    </content>
